{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the only question was where to get the necessary funds, because my parents' income had definitely been affected by the Nazi boycott of the store.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the B'nai B'rith, the state organization of the B'nai B'rith in the state of Baden gave me a-- a grant to purchase the tickets.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But all this was something that was done and had become very similar to what was happening in Jewish families all over who did want to utilize the first chance they had to get out of the country.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, as long as they had an income, they felt that this was where they would hold out until what they considered the inevitable end of this Nazi nonsense.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That that end would not come until another World War was something that was only vaguely feared, but did not look like a reality.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not yet.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not only that, they-- they traveled with me as far as Mannheim, which was the next largest city, where I caught the train for-- for Paris, where-- and I met the other four-- three of the other four students in Paris.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The fifth one was not to join us until Southampton, where the-- where the ship stopped.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- oh, through France I don't think we needed a transit visa, but if we did, we had it, yes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was routine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By ship from Le Havre, France, with a stop in Southampton to New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Was the Britannic, a Cunard liner.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "10 days.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We left on September 5 from Le Havre, stopped in Southampton on the next day, and then arrived in New York on the 15th of September.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was almost 20.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
